The provided Kotlin code violates the **Single Responsibility Principle (SRP)**. Each class (`EmailService`, `SMSService`, and `EmailClient`) is responsible for handling multiple types of notifications, which it doesn't fully support. This leads to methods throwing `UnsupportedOperationException` when called with unsupported notification types.

To refactor this code in compliance with the Single Responsibility Principle, we should separate each type of notification into its own interface and class. Here's how you can do that:

```kotlin
// Interfaces for sending notifications
interface EmailSender {
    fun sendEmail(recipient: String, subject: String, body: String)
}

interface SMSSender {
    fun sendSMS(phoneNumber: String, message: String)
}

interface PushNotificationSender {
    fun sendPushNotification(deviceId: String, title: String, message: String)
}

interface SlackMessageSender {
    fun sendSlackMessage(channel: String, message: String)
}

// Interfaces for receiving notifications
interface EmailReceiver {
    fun receiveEmail(sender: String, subject: String, body: String)
}

interface SMSReceiver {
    fun receiveSMS(sender: String, message: String)
}

interface PushNotificationReceiver {
    fun receivePushNotification(appId: String, title: String, message: String)
}

interface SlackMessageReceiver {
    fun receiveSlackMessage(sender: String, message: String)
}

// Implementations for sending notifications
class EmailService : EmailSender {
    override fun sendEmail(recipient: String, subject: String, body: String) {
        println("Sending email to $recipient with subject: $subject")
    }
}

class SMSService : SMSSender {
    override fun sendSMS(phoneNumber: String, message: String) {
        println("Sending SMS to $phoneNumber: $message")
    }
}

// Implementations for receiving notifications
class EmailClient : EmailReceiver {
    override fun receiveEmail(sender: String, subject: String, body: String) {
        println("Received email from $sender with subject: $subject")
    }
}
```

In this refactored code:
- Each notification type (email, SMS, push notification, Slack message) has its own interface for sending and receiving.
- The `EmailService` class only implements the `EmailSender` interface, focusing solely on email notifications.
- The `SMSService` class only implements the `SMSSender` interface, focusing solely on SMS notifications.
- The `EmailClient` class only implements the `EmailReceiver` interface, focusing solely on receiving emails.

This separation ensures that each class has a single responsibility and adheres to the Single Responsibility Principle.

